               <p>GEORGE BERKELEY HARRISON. I am a <rs id="t18280911-13-viclabel70" type="occupation">wine-merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-13-victim163 t18280911-13-viclabel70"></join>. On the 9th of September, about ten minutes to five o'clock in the evening, I was on <placeName id="t18280911-13-crimeloc71">London-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-13-crimeloc71" type="placeName" value="London-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-13-crimeloc71" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-13-off68 t18280911-13-crimeloc71"></join>, going towards the Borough, and felt a sudden jerk at my pocket; I turned round, and found myself in contact with the prisoner pass my handkerchief to the other, who was preparing to put it into his breast; I seized him, gave him to another to hold while I pursued the prisoner; he was taken in my sight and given into my hands; when I returned the other had got away.</p>
